OL,3,C'Pain and hurt' of Donaldson's alleged
OL,4,Cvictims 'still so visible', court told
OL,6,FLady Donaldson, 60, denies several
OL,7,Fcharges of aiding and abetting her
OL,8,Fhusband's alleged offending.
OL,10,FShe is facing a trial of the facts on
OL,11,Fmental health grounds. That will test
OL,12,Fthe evidence in the case, but cannot
OL,13,Fresult in a criminal conviction.
OL,15,FBeginning her closing submissions to
OL,16,Fthe jury of seven men and five women,
OL,17,FMs Walsh said the jury would have a
OL,18,F"good understanding of what the
OL,19,Fevidence is in this case".
OL,26,@zD@AOU{D@YO]
