OL,3,C'Pain and hurt' of Donaldson's alleged
OL,4,Cvictims 'still so visible', court told
OL,6,F"The topic remained untouched, the
OL,7,Fhornet's nest avoided."
OL,9,FReferring to an incident in which
OL,10,FComplainant A alleges Donaldson had
OL,11,Fused a light to look at her private
OL,12,Fparts, the barrister said Lady
OL,13,FDonaldson had been told but that the
OL,14,Fincident was "brushed under the
OL,15,Fcarpet".
OL,17,FShe said years later, Complainant A
OL,18,Fhad told her husband about the alleged
OL,19,Fabuse to give him the "option of
OL,20,Fwalking away" from the relationship if
OL,21,Fhe chose to.
