OL,3,C'Pain and hurt' of Donaldson's alleged
OL,4,Cvictims 'still so visible', court told
OL,6,FReferring again to the light incident
OL,7,Finvolving Complainant A, Ms Walsh said
OL,8,Fthe alleged victim was "certain she
OL,9,Fknew he was looking at her private
OL,10,Fparts with a light".
OL,12,FShe said Donaldson had been "caught in
OL,13,Fthe act", adding "he knew he had no
OL,14,Fexplanation".
OL,16,FThe barrister then turned to a letter
OL,17,Fwritten by Donaldson to Complainant A
OL,18,Fin 2020 where he referred to "being in
OL,19,Fa deep pit of sin" and of causing
OL,20,F"deep wounds".
